/etc/velo -- velo install audit + level config (M2).

This directory is shipped by site79.tgz and survives into the booted system as
an audit record of how this box was provisioned.

Contents:
  answers          per-install TUI choices (profile/startmode/pkgs/...), written
                   by velo-install BEFORE install.site runs; PARSED (never
                   sourced -- the file is data, never executed, to avoid an RCE
                   vector) + re-validated by install.site. Mode 0600.
                   Absent -> safe floor minimal+L1.
  pf/              the three level pf.conf variants (pf.l1/l2/l3.conf). install.site
                   copies the chosen one to /etc/pf.conf; the others stay here for
                   the future v0.2 L1/L2/L3 switcher.
  sysctl/          per-level sysctl deltas (sysctl.l1/l2/l3.conf), APPENDED to
                   /etc/sysctl.conf by install.site (never overwriting the base).

Nothing here is secret. The FDE passphrase is never written to the target.
